    "summary": "Freesound.org exposes one developer integration surface: the Freesound API v2 HTTP API, documented on freesound.org with a known OpenAPI spec on APIs.guru; it supports token-based API key auth for general access and OAuth2 bearer tokens for user-authorized/write operations.",
    "description": "Freesound is an online collaborative database of sound recordings and audio clips. It lets users search, preview, download, and contribute sounds, packs, and related metadata.",
    "credentials": {
      "freesound_api_credential": {
        "type": "compound",
        "label": "Freesound API credential (client ID, client secret/API key, redirect URL)",
        "generateUrl": "https://freesound.org/apiv2/apply/",
        "setup": "Create a Freesound account, then go to [API credential request](https://freesound.org/apiv2/apply/) and request an API credential. The docs say the credential page shows a `Client id` plus a `Client secret/Api key` value; for simple token auth you use the `Client secret/Api key`, and for OAuth2 authorization-code flow you use the `client_id` and `client_secret` from the same credential. Configure the credential's redirect URL there if you will use OAuth2.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "freesound_oauth_access_token": {
        "type": "oauth2",
        "label": "Freesound OAuth2 access token",
        "generateUrl": "https://freesound.org/apiv2/apply/",
        "setup": "First request a Freesound API credential at [API credential request](https://freesound.org/apiv2/apply/). Then implement the OAuth2 authorization-code flow described in [Authentication](https://freesound.org/docs/api/authentication.html): send users to `https://freesound.org/apiv2/oauth2/authorize/` with `client_id` and `response_type=code`, then exchange the returned code at `https://freesound.org/apiv2/oauth2/access_token/` using your `client_id` and `client_secret` to obtain an access token. Freesound states OAuth2 requests must be made over `https`.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      }
    },
